dren&#8217;s needs and developmental abilities. This paper describes and illustrates a new approach for creating user abstractions of children called the child-persona technique. Child-personas integrate theoretical concepts, empirically generated data and experiential goals. An analysis of the utility of this technique provides insights about how this technique can benefit designers by generating realistic child-user abstractions through a process which supports designers in child-centric design.\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"prism.issn\" content=\"1435-5566\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"prism.publicationName\" content=\"Cognition, Technology &amp; Work\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"prism.publicationDate\" content=\"2007-04-11\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"prism.volume\" content=\"10\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"prism.number\" content=\"2\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"prism.section\" content=\"OriginalPaper\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"prism.startingPage\" content=\"155\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"prism.endingPage\" content=\"166\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"prism.copyright\" content=\"2007 Springer-Verlag London Limited\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"prism.rightsAgent\" content=\"journalpermissions@springernature.com\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"prism.url\" content=\"https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10111-007-0071-2\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"prism.doi\" content=\"doi:10.1007/s10111-007-0071-2\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"citation_pdf_url\" content=\"https://link.springer.com/content/pdf/10.1007/s10111-007-0071-2.pdf\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"citation_fulltext_html_url\" content=\"https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10111-007-0071-2\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"citation_journal_title\" content=\"Cognition, Technology &amp; Work\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"citation_journal_abbrev\" content=\"Cogn Tech Work\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"citation_publisher\" content=\"Springer-Verlag\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"citation_issn\" content=\"1435-5566\"/>\n\n    <meta name=\"citation_title\" content=\"Child-based personas: need, ability and ex